extinction.note:
Exinction due to Galatic absorption to be applied to the TDE light.
E(B-V) based on from maps of Schlegel, Finkbeiner & Davis (1998).
We use a blackbody with T=3e4K to find the linear extinction in each optical/UV band (similar to A_nu), 
we also give the ratio of total-to-selective extinction (R_nu)

host.note:
The "observations" key constains the observed magnitudes, corrected for Galactic extinction. 
The "model" key containts output from Prospector with FSPS (e.g., stellar mass). 
Each parameter is [median, lower, upper] range of the 68%CL interval.
We also give the synthetic observed magnitudes, these are also corrected for Galactic extinction. 
To reverse the Galactic extinction correction, use the "R_nu" key.
Parameters with .0 indicate magnitudes in the galaxy rest-frame.

lightcurve.note:
The flux is not corrected for Galactic extinction, but the extinction correction 
per band is provided in this dataframe (under the "extinction" key). 
MJD is as observed (ie, no correction for time dilation)
